    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but its not just about \"sensitivity\" or being anxious. i've been looking into neuro-aesthetics and how certain geometric frequencies can mess with brain waves. it feels way more intentional than a coincidence. like, why would they all use this exact same tight, repetitive grid? it feels less like fashion and more like a tool for calming people down so they dont protest or question anything. doesnt that sound like a real way to use social engineering?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
