      "content": "exactly. and it's not just about \"soothing\" for the sake of it. if you think about how much of our lives are spent in retail environments or wearing these brands, even a tiny decrease in a person's ability to resist or think critically over time would be massive. if big corporations or even governments wanted to keep a population passive, wouldn't mass-producing specific visual frequencies in common clothing be one of the most efficient ways to do it? it's like they're hiding the control mechanism in plain sight.",
